headshotImage.caption: Gary Brent player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Gary Brent player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: uses his feet, down the pitch and lofted straight over the bowlers head to finish off the victory for South Africa

commentPostTextItems.html: A win for South AFrica but not as convincing as they would have thought. Some encouraging batting from the youngsters but a lot of work to do in the bowling department.
For Zimbabwe 5 run outs in an innings will be at the top of their topics for discussion while some work in the field has to be done.
We hope that you will join us again on Saturday for the second match from Harare

commentTextItems.html: full toss on the off as he came down the pitch, lofts that a few bounces wide of long-off
all defensive on the off, short cover gathers
gets well forward and plays down the line towards mid-on

defends from line and length to the off

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Pollock b Philander 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: WHAT A CATCH, Williams gets one sliding across him, goes on the drive, gets the edge, the old man Pollock takes off to his left, dives full length to snatch a one handed left hand catch out of the air

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Philander 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Matsikenyeri is drawn well forward on the front foot, a touch outside off, the off cutter bites, slips through between bat and pad and sends the off stump flying

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor run out (Bodi/†de Villiers) 19 (56b 1x4 0x6 83m) SR: 33.92

dismissalComment.html: fullish ball is flicked off the toes towards and wide of Bodi at fine leg, Taylor attempts to beat the return but TV finds him well short of a good return from Bodi to the keeper
